An Act to allow for school districts to collect a fee associated with nonresident pupil
transportation.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 8A of Chapter 74 of the general laws, as appearing in the 2016 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by striking out the section and inserting in place thereof the following:-
3 Section 8A. A school district may charge a fee for transportation for students in grades 7-
4 12 who attend an out of district vocational or agricultural school; said fee may not exceed the fee
5 charged to students in grades 7-12 who attend an in district school, provided that no fee shall be
6 required for students whose families are at or below 300% of the federal poverty level as defined
7 by the federal Department of Health and Human Services.
